<h2><span id="5._d3">5. d3</span></h2>
<p>Though passive and harmless-looking, this move defends the e4-pawn and makes Bxc6 followed by Nxe5 a reality. Therefore, Black has to loosen his queenside with 5...b5. White doesn't want to attack immediately. He wants to attack after building an impregnable fortress that offers no chances for counterplay. 
</p>
